[1] South Korea, 5 new cases - MOH 4 Jun 2015
Date: 4 Jun 2015
Source: Korean MOH 4 Jun 2015 [machine trans., edited]
http://www.mw.go.kr/front_new/al/sal0301vw.jsp?PAR_MENU_ID=04&MENU_ID=0403&page=1&CONT_SEQ=322967


An additional 5 patients were confirmed with MERS-CoV infection

- Three patients had contact with the index patient's hospital B

- The remaining 2 patients had been admitted to the same hospital ward as patient 16 in hospital E

[unclear machine translation here but seems to say there are 14 confirmed individuals who had contact with health professionals that worked in the medical institutions where MERS-CoV infected patients were admitted.]
 
The Department of Health and Human Services' central management task force announced on Thurs 4 Jun 2015 there 5 additional cases were confirmed as positive for MERS-CoV infection.
 
Of the 3 patients that were admitted to hospital B, all 3 were in medical wards during the period 15-17 May 2015 when the index case was admitted there.

Of the other 2 patients, one was in the same ward in hospital E 28-30 May 2015 while case no.16 was hospitalized there, and the other a physician who had contact with case no.14 at hospital D on 27 May 2015 and had a fever.

Listing of 5 newly confirmed cases on 4 Jun 2015:
Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS)

[see section [2] below for complete list of confirmed cases in Koreans. - Mod.MPP]

