[In the latest report of the MOH for 4 Jun 2015 (due to time zone change it is now AM of 4 Jun 2015 in S. Korea), there were an additional 5 cases confirmed with MERS-CoV infection in South Korea bringing the total number of cases reported in South Koreans to 35. Three of the 5 cases are secondary cases, having been in hospital B at the same time the index case was admitted there, and two of the cases a)re tertiary cases, having had contact with secondary cases (case no.14 while admitted to hospital D and case no.16 in hospital E. Of the 5 newly confirmed cases, 2 were healthcare personnel (a media report submitted by ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iikura classified them as physicians http://www.arirang.co.kr/News/News_View.asp?nseq=180199). There have now been 5 tertiary cases reported.

The HealthMap/ProMED map of South Korea can be found at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3407535,195. - Mod.MPP]

