[2] South Korea, 5 new cases - MOH 3 Jun 2015
Date: 3 Jun 2015
Source: Korean MOH 3 Jun 2015
http://www.mw.go.kr/front_new/al/sal0301vw.jsp?PAR_MENU_ID=04&MENU_ID=0403&page=1&CONT_SEQ=322848


An additional 5 [MERS] patients have been confirmed, bringing the total number of Korean cases to 30 including 2 deaths.

Of the 5 newly confirmed cases [today, 3 Jun 2015]:
- 4 patients are secondary cases associated with spread in the 2nd hospital [hospital B] where the index case was admitted, involving medical patients or family members, all of whom had contact with the 1st patient (the index case) (or in the same ward as the index case).
- One patient is a tertiary case associated with contact with case No. 16 .

Of these 4 patients referred to above as secondary cases, all were at the hospital between 15 and 17 May 2015, either hospitalized or visiting a family member who was hospitalized in the same ward as the index case.

The other 1 patient was in the hospital from 22- 28 May 2015 in the same ward as one of the secondary cases (case No.16). [Hence, it is referred to as a tertiary case.]

